        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 29 at 8:01PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 800 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of The Intersection Of Ranch Road 1828 And Ranch Road
915, or 13 miles south of Mertzon, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Christoval.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
